    <p>• These are meant to en­er­gise vis­i­tors.</p>
    <p>• These plants need strong sun­light to flour­ish, and this is why the ther­a­peu­tic gar­den can­not be com­pletely shaded. • There are also other plants in the gar­den, in­clud­ing plants with fa­mil­iar smells like the pan­dan, which can evoke the mem­o­ries of vis­i­tors.</p>
    <p>Red-flow­ered sea grape, known as coc­coloba ru­gosa, is unique to this ther­a­peu­tic gar­den.</p>

